1. use k8s docs to create a pv, make sure that the storageclass: ""
    a. size = 10M
    b. name = database-volume
    c. reclaim policy = retain
    hostpath:
     type: Directoyr
     path: /mnt/data
2. use k8s docs to create a pvc, make sure that the storageclass: ""
    a. size = 10M 
    b. name = database-claim 
3. create a pod using mysql:9.4 image
   a. nodeName: <name of the node>
   b. use the pvc created in point 2 
   c. search where mysql stores it's (which directory inside the container )
      and mount the volume in this directory
